com.nutiteq.components
Class Constraints

java.lang.Object
  com.nutiteq.components.Constraints

public class Constraints
extends java.lang.Object

Specification for various map manipulations constraints. These constraints will be used by both, the MapView map manipulation API, and the user interface.

getTiltRange

public Range getTiltRange()
Gets the current tilt range. The minimum and maximum values are in degrees.

Returns:
the current tilt range

setTiltRange

public void setTiltRange(Range tiltRange)
Sets the new tilt range. The minimum tilt range is 30 degrees and the maximum is 90 degrees. Values that are out of range are capped.

Parameters:
tiltRange - the new tilt range

getZoomRange

public Range getZoomRange()
Gets the current zoom range.

Returns:
the current zoom range

setZoomRange

public void setZoomRange(Range zoomRange)
Sets the new zoom range. The minimum zoom value is 0 and the maximum is 24. Values that are out of range are capped.

Parameters:
zoomRange - the new zoom range

getMapBounds

public Bounds getMapBounds()
Gets the current map bounds. Bounds left, top, right and bottom values are in the current base map's projection.

Returns:
the current map bounds. Can be null when bounds are not defined.

setMapBounds

public void setMapBounds(Bounds bounds)
Sets new map bounds. Bounds left, top, right and bottom values are in the current base map's projection. If the bounds are larger than the world size, they will be capped to world bounds.

Parameters:
bounds - the new map bounds (can be null)

isRotatable

public boolean isRotatable()
Test if rotation is activated.

Returns:
can rotate map view with dual-touch gesture

setRotatable

public void setRotatable(boolean rotatable)
Set map view rotation on/off. Default is on.

Parameters:
rotatable - flag to turn rotation on/off.
